Co-spatial: this is the most viable scenario that has been discussed below in two-steps. Generally, the origin of blazar variability may be associated with the shocks. However, minute-scale variability from a re-confinement shock during fast flare F2 is difficult to reconcile with the shock-in-jet scenario. To better understand this, we estimate the cross-sectional radius of the re-confinement shock Rrcs~2.5×10−2.5Lj1046ergs−1(dBLR/0.1pc)−1pc\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
